Get Data Elements Metadata

Source: R/get_data_elements_metadata.R
get_data_elements_metadata.Rd

get_data_elements_metadata() fetches data elements metadata from the KHIS API server, including their IDs and names.

get_data_elements_metadata(element_ids = NULL, ...)

Arguments

element_ids

A vector of specific data element IDs to retrieve. If NULL, all data elements will be retrieved.

...

Other options that can be passed onto .api_get.

Value

A tibble containing the following columns:

  • element_id - The unique identifier for the data element.

  • element - The name of the data element.

See also

.api_get() for making API call to KHIS server

Examples

if (FALSE) { # khis_has_cred()
# Fetch the data element metadata for particular element id
data <- get_data_elements_metadata(element_ids = c('htFuvGJRW1X'))
data

# Fetch all the data elements
data <- get_data_elements_metadata()
data
}
